entries.title: 24 star Annie Wersching dies at the age of 45
entries.description: Actor Annie Wersching, best known for playing FBI agent Renee Walker in the series 24 has died at the age of 45.

entries.title: Six British children discovered in abandoned wine cellar in Austria
entries.description: Six British children have been taken into care in Austria after they were found to have been living in an abandoned wine cellar with their parents.

entries.title: Four dead in New Zealand after record rainfall causes flooding and landslides
entries.description: Four people have died as torrential rain continues to hammer New Zealand's largest city, causing flash flooding and landslides.

entries.title: Djokovic wins Australian Open a year after deportation - equals Nadal's Grand Slam record
entries.description: Novak Djokovic has won the Australian Open to equal Rafael Nadal's Grand Slam record, a year after he was deported over his COVID vaccination status.

entries.title: Ten children die after boat capsizes - rescue operation under way
entries.description: Ten children have died after a boat capsized in northwest Pakistan.

entries.title: 40 dead after bus falls into ravine
entries.description: 40 people have died after a bus fell into a ravine in Balochistan in Pakistan, local media reported.

entries.title: Netanyahu vows to 'strengthen' West Bank settlements after shooting attacks
entries.description: Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says he plans to "strengthen the settlements" in the West Bank in response to two shootings which left seven people dead and five wounded.
